1
00:00:20,383 --> 00:00:21,560
I beg your forgiveness

2
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:22,657
about your sister.

3
00:00:23,010 --> 00:00:24,760
Your Highness, we are under ambush.

4
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:26,440
There is nothing I can do.

5
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,480
Father, Mother, Sister cannot come anymore.

6
00:00:33,530 --> 00:00:34,531
I am my father's son,

7
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:37,640
the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi.

8
00:00:37,963 --> 00:00:39,164
Crown Prince,

9
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:42,760
lead the army to reclaim the City of Ayutthaya at all costs.

10
00:00:43,103 --> 00:00:45,204
It is a duty I have carried since birth.

11
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:47,360
Duty is like the mist

12
00:00:48,010 --> 00:00:49,280
that obscures the sun.

13
00:00:50,017 --> 00:00:51,841
The prayers of us both,

14
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:53,920
therefore, can never come true.

15
00:00:55,163 --> 00:00:56,164
From this moment forth,

16
00:00:56,717 --> 00:00:58,600
we shall each fulfill our own duty.

17
00:00:59,637 --> 00:01:01,880
I hereby revoke our oath,

18
00:01:02,917 --> 00:01:04,918
that the two of us shall never harm one another.

19
00:01:06,110 --> 00:01:07,240
Should we ever meet,

20
00:01:08,417 --> 00:01:09,360
let neither of us

21
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,440
stay our hand.

22
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:14,480
I have something important to tell you.

23
00:01:14,990 --> 00:01:15,991
- What?
- What?

24
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:18,000
Is his horoscope truly so fatal?

25
00:01:19,643 --> 00:01:21,000
Phra Maha Thera Khanchong has prophesied that,

26
00:01:21,657 --> 00:01:23,240
between this year and the next,

27
00:01:24,177 --> 00:01:27,440
the Crown Prince shall surely perish on the battlefield.

28
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,121
Moreover,

29
00:01:30,303 --> 00:01:32,240
Prince Ekathosarot has issued a royal command

30
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,760
for me to inform you all.

31
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,240
Since the heavens are now in our favor,

32
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:41,360
In this upcoming battle, he asked that the three of you

33
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,760
unite your hearts and strength

34
00:01:44,041 --> 00:01:46,620
to slay the Crown Prince by any means necessary.

35
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:12,751
I am sorry.

36
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,000
This wound has missed your vitals.

37
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,840
It shall only prevent you from wielding a sword in battle.

38
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,520
Consider this wound

39
00:02:54,497 --> 00:02:57,640
a token of goodwill from your younger brother.

40
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,111
You.

41
00:03:25,877 --> 00:03:27,920
No, Your Majesty! Please spare their lives!

42
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:31,160
Mingyi Swa was wounded

43
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,120
and forced to retreat,

44
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,641
withdrawing his troops back to Hongsawadi.

45
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,920
This incited the ultimate fury of King Nanda Bayin.

46
00:03:40,283 --> 00:03:41,284
Soldiers,

47
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,560
take them both and behead them!

48
00:03:43,597 --> 00:03:45,040
Let me never see their faces again!

49
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,520
Spare our lives,

50
00:03:46,617 --> 00:03:49,200
I beg of you, Your Majesty, please spare our lives.

51
00:04:05,103 --> 00:04:06,440
Mingyi Swa

52
00:04:07,323 --> 00:04:09,000
was also severely punished.

53
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:55,160
If you were not my son,

54
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,800
I would have your head taken just as they were.

55
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:15,960
Stay here and face your punishment.

56
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,001
Do not show your face to anyone,

57
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:23,160
lest they mock you, saying that a crown prince

58
00:06:23,610 --> 00:06:26,120
is as cowardly as if he were not a man.

59
00:06:44,677 --> 00:06:48,137
If you repent, come forth in women's clothing to beg my forgiveness,

60
00:06:48,217 --> 00:06:49,480
and then, I shall pardon you.

61
00:07:29,163 --> 00:07:30,457
How pitiful.

62
00:07:31,563 --> 00:07:33,720
He ordered the execution of the generals

63
00:07:33,863 --> 00:07:35,480
who accompanied the prince.

64
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:37,720
They were slaughtered in great numbers, Your Highness.

65
00:07:39,703 --> 00:07:42,880
King Nanda Bayin grows more cruel by the day.

66
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,520
If we remain in Hongsawadi,

67
00:07:46,863 --> 00:07:48,521
we shall surely face danger

68
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:51,480
from the fires of his wrath.

69
00:08:09,397 --> 00:08:11,920
Drag every man in this room out at once.

70
00:08:13,957 --> 00:08:17,100
King Nanda Bayin rounded up the people,

71
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:20,760
preparing for war against Ayutthaya once more.

72
00:08:32,203 --> 00:08:33,204
Go, get up!

73
00:08:33,317 --> 00:08:34,400
- Get up!
- Get up!

74
00:08:34,837 --> 00:08:35,838
- I will not go!
- Do not cry!

75
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,100
Don't cry! Go!

76
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:40,000
Don't cry! Go!

77
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:45,560
Do not take my child! Please, do not take my child away!

78
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:50,960
Causing great suffering

79
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,840
to every citizen across the land.

80
00:09:02,983 --> 00:09:04,720
- Here!
- Go!

81
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:07,411
Go!

82
00:09:07,477 --> 00:09:08,480
- Come!
- Come with me!

83
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:09,651
Come now!

84
00:09:10,203 --> 00:09:12,080
- Go!
- Go!

85
00:09:14,537 --> 00:09:15,920
Wrap yourself in the saffron robes immediately.

86
00:10:04,717 --> 00:10:06,400
Please eat something, Your Highness.

87
00:10:18,837 --> 00:10:20,200
You have not eaten

88
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,080
nor slept for months.

89
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:38,560
How is the situation outside?

90
00:10:57,083 --> 00:10:58,084
What matter

91
00:11:00,710 --> 00:11:02,840
has caused you such profound sorrow?

92
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,920
King Nanda Bayin

93
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,000
has ordered a mass mobilization for war.

94
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:25,680
young and old alike have been rounded up,

95
00:11:31,243 --> 00:11:34,760
even the monks living in temples were not spared.

96
00:11:47,577 --> 00:11:48,920
A king wages war

97
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:53,671
to protect his people,

98
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:00,280
but if waging war

99
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,960
brings only hardship to the people of Hongsawadi,

100
00:12:08,043 --> 00:12:09,400
for what purpose is it done?

101
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:13,961
At this hour,

102
00:12:15,210 --> 00:12:16,720
King Nanda Bayin

103
00:12:19,011 --> 00:12:21,960
thinks not of Hongsawadi in the least.

104
00:12:26,970 --> 00:12:29,560
His heart is consumed only by the desire for war

105
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:33,400
to seek vengeance against Ayutthaya.

106
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:43,720
Will the empire my father fought to build

107
00:12:47,957 --> 00:12:50,760
truly end in such a way?

108
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:28,724
Brother.

109
00:13:29,477 --> 00:13:31,360
Hongsawadi does not lack brave men,

110
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,200
but it lacks a righteous king.

111
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:37,360
You must preserve your life and wait for the day you ascend to the throne.

112
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,840
For only you

113
00:13:40,450 --> 00:13:43,277
can extinguish the fires of war and bring peace to the realm.

114
00:14:07,823 --> 00:14:10,120
May it please Your Majesty,

115
00:14:12,177 --> 00:14:15,640
Crown Prince Mingyi Swa requests an audience.

116
00:14:15,937 --> 00:14:17,760
He seeks your royal audience, Your Majesty.

117
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,721
Tell him to enter.

118
00:14:21,203 --> 00:14:22,204
Yes, Your Majesty.

119
00:15:06,310 --> 00:15:07,311
Mingyi Swa.

120
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,481
Son.

121
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:27,120
May it please Your Majesty,

122
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,440
I, Mingyi Swa,

123
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:33,360
Crown Prince of Hongsawadi,

124
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:37,750
am mindful of my failure and neglect of duty.

125
00:15:40,817 --> 00:15:42,000
Therefore, I humbly ask

126
00:15:43,297 --> 00:15:44,800
for your royal permission

127
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:48,641
to lead the army into battle against Ayutthaya

128
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:51,770
to redeem my honor, Your Majesty.

129
00:16:02,863 --> 00:16:03,864
What was that?

130
00:16:05,550 --> 00:16:06,960
You are volunteering for battle?

131
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,281
Yes, Your Majesty.

132
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:19,520
I volunteer

133
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,040
to fight with all my might.

134
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,820
If I do not return victorious, I shall not return at all.

135
00:16:42,897 --> 00:16:45,560
Mingyi Swa, my son.

136
00:16:47,130 --> 00:16:48,440
this truly gladdens my heart.

137
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,881
For heaven's sake!

138
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:52,520
The Hongsawadi army is marching once again.

139
00:17:55,643 --> 00:17:57,560
The Crown Prince himself leads the troops.

140
00:18:03,983 --> 00:18:04,984
This time,

141
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:08,720
Would it be better if I led the army in your stead?

142
00:18:08,817 --> 00:18:09,818
Why?

143
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:13,360
You and the Crown Prince

144
00:18:14,983 --> 00:18:16,560
have known each other since you were small children.

145
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,901
If it comes to a fight to the death,

146
00:18:24,863 --> 00:18:26,164
will you truly be able to do it?

147
00:18:31,753 --> 00:18:35,800
I am the commander-in-chief. Why would I be unable to do such a thing?

148
00:19:17,337 --> 00:19:18,480
Do you truly believe

149
00:19:21,877 --> 00:19:23,000
that I will die?

150
00:19:28,257 --> 00:19:30,880
Such a matter is not worth the risk.

151
00:19:36,203 --> 00:19:37,304
To go out to battle,

152
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:41,720
If death comes not today, it shall come on a day to follow.

153
00:19:47,683 --> 00:19:48,960
For us to fall by each other's hands

154
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,160
is better than dying at the hand of another.

155
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,441
Nares.

156
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:12,320
If I must truly die,

157
00:20:17,317 --> 00:20:18,840
I ask to die by your hand.

158
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,041
Very well.

159
00:20:46,743 --> 00:20:47,880
Come out and fight,

160
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:51,800
Then let us see how it ends.

161
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:25,311
May it please Your Majesty,

162
00:21:27,130 --> 00:21:29,800
the King of Prome and the royal tutor Mangjaparo

163
00:21:29,937 --> 00:21:31,600
have arrived with their troops to join the forces.

164
00:21:53,463 --> 00:21:55,164
I pay my humble respects, Your Majesty.

165
00:21:59,023 --> 00:22:00,440
Now everyone is gathered together.

166
00:22:04,537 --> 00:22:05,538
Mingyi Hnaung.

167
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,520
I hear you are now the King of Prome.

168
00:22:10,650 --> 00:22:12,080
I suppose I must pay you my respects.

169
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,201
No need, Brother.

170
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,600
you may speak to me as you always have.

171
00:22:24,890 --> 00:22:26,560
Father must not trust me,

172
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,400
which is why he sent you all, is it not?

173
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:35,120
Father fears that you may be overexerting yourself,

174
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:37,800
so he sent us to help with the fighting instead.

175
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:40,120
And it is not just us,

176
00:22:41,763 --> 00:22:43,480
the army from Toungoo has also arrived.

177
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,001
[Natshinnaung, the son of the King of Toungoo.]

178
00:23:05,517 --> 00:23:06,518
Your Highness.

179
00:23:07,957 --> 00:23:08,958
Natshinnaung.

180
00:23:11,983 --> 00:23:13,880
Did you lead the army down from Toungoo yourself?

181
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:15,880
I come in my father's stead.

182
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:19,400
the King of Hongsawadi has commanded

183
00:23:20,917 --> 00:23:22,120
that in this war,

184
00:23:23,283 --> 00:23:24,500
victory is the only option.

185
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,960
Defeat is not permitted.

186
00:25:41,017 --> 00:25:42,520
How is Muang?

187
00:25:50,103 --> 00:25:53,080
He is quite stubborn this time.

188
00:25:53,730 --> 00:25:57,320
Aside from myself, no one can get near him at all, Your Majesty.

189
00:25:59,617 --> 00:26:02,400
If Muang turns unruly during the battle,

190
00:26:03,737 --> 00:26:05,400
Your Majesty will be in great danger.

191
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,520
Please change your royal mount, Your Majesty.

192
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,160
Do you wish to go with me?

193
00:27:24,063 --> 00:27:25,440
My good boy.

194
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,481
[Battlefield of Nong Sarai]

195
00:27:48,530 --> 00:27:49,840
My army

196
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:54,880
and the army of the Crown Prince engaged in a fierce melee since late morning.

197
00:28:10,137 --> 00:28:13,560
Muang grew enraged until he could no longer be controlled,

198
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:18,360
bolting away without any direction.

199
00:28:39,537 --> 00:28:43,240
The troops and the four-fold guardians could not keep up.

200
00:28:47,723 --> 00:28:50,680
Only the royal elephant of Prince Ekathosarot

201
00:28:51,177 --> 00:28:52,600
managed to follow closely behind.

202
00:29:43,143 --> 00:29:44,760
And when the dust and smoke cleared,

203
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,200
I discovered that

204
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:50,040
we two brothers

205
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:53,300
were surrounded by the soldiers of Hongsawadi.

206
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,560
Let's go, Muang.

207
00:31:59,123 --> 00:32:00,124
Brother.

208
00:32:03,570 --> 00:32:04,571
Brother.

209
00:32:07,370 --> 00:32:09,160
Since you have wandered into such a circle,

210
00:32:11,083 --> 00:32:13,320
the Hongsawadi forces have bows and firearms.

211
00:32:16,803 --> 00:32:18,560
How will you ever break your way out?

212
00:32:22,697 --> 00:32:23,698
I must simply try.

213
00:32:25,997 --> 00:32:28,360
Perhaps Phra Maha Thera Khanchong’s prophecy was mistaken.

214
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:31,520
Maybe it is not I

215
00:32:32,923 --> 00:32:34,250
who must die in this battle.

216
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:38,841
In that case,

217
00:32:40,123 --> 00:32:41,880
I shall congratulate you.

218
00:32:45,717 --> 00:32:46,718
And you?

219
00:32:52,550 --> 00:32:55,600
A warrior dying on the battlefield

220
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:57,961
is nothing out of the ordinary.

221
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,760
Didn't you tell me that yourself?

222
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:06,601
From this day

223
00:33:08,797 --> 00:33:10,400
until the days to come,

224
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,320
there will likely be no warrior

225
00:33:17,850 --> 00:33:18,960
as brave as you.

226
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:27,040
How could I let you die

227
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:30,521
at the hands of mere common soldiers?

228
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:36,801
If so,

229
00:33:38,930 --> 00:33:40,520
I invite you

230
00:33:41,763 --> 00:33:43,800
to join me in an elephant duel.

231
00:33:45,230 --> 00:33:46,480
Should I meet my end

232
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,600
at your hands,

233
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:52,240
I shall have no regrets.

234
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:13,120
I, Mingyi Swa,

235
00:34:15,450 --> 00:34:17,960
the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi,

236
00:34:19,970 --> 00:34:21,600
shall engage in a royal duel on elephant back

237
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,720
with Prince Nares of Ayutthaya,

238
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:27,200
so that the honor of this deed

239
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:29,840
shall remain known forevermore.

240
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:13,281
Sure.

241
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:29,601
Enough.

242
00:36:30,970 --> 00:36:31,971
I am tired now.

243
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:34,720
If you are tired, then surrender.

244
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,881
- I shall not lose.
- I shall not lose either.

245
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:39,601
Very well.

246
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,520
Fight then, with all your might.

247
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,281
Brother.

248
00:37:15,310 --> 00:37:16,920
No matter who wins or loses,

249
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,680
there shall be no room for regret.

250
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,601
In the past,

251
00:40:20,217 --> 00:40:21,808
I believed that war

252
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:25,000
was simply about killing strangers

253
00:40:26,083 --> 00:40:27,840
or those not of our kind.

254
00:40:32,090 --> 00:40:35,240
But in the reality of battle, be it a friend,

255
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,801
a brother,

256
00:40:37,330 --> 00:40:39,280
or someone you once knew so well,

257
00:40:40,437 --> 00:40:44,480
if they stand on the opposite side, you must be prepared to kill them.

258
00:40:47,083 --> 00:40:48,640
We grew up together.

259
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,440
I loved you like my own brother.

260
00:40:55,470 --> 00:40:59,160
I, too, saw you as my own elder brother.

261
00:41:02,797 --> 00:41:03,798
We both

262
00:41:05,270 --> 00:41:07,120
were meant to stay on the same side forever.

263
00:41:08,223 --> 00:41:09,224
Was that not the promise?

264
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:12,600
If you stand by my side,

265
00:41:14,097 --> 00:41:15,398
I shall stand by yours.

266
00:41:18,477 --> 00:41:19,960
This is my solemn oath.

267
00:41:23,643 --> 00:41:25,080
This is my solemn oath.

268
00:41:37,950 --> 00:41:41,320
- I pray that our two lands...
- I pray that our two lands…

269
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,440
- May dwell together in enduring peace.
- May dwell together in enduring peace.

270
00:41:46,250 --> 00:41:48,121
- Bound as brothers, kin of the same soul.
- Bound as brothers, kin of the same soul.

271
00:41:49,870 --> 00:41:50,871
- For all eternity.
- For all eternity.

272
00:42:41,163 --> 00:42:42,164
From this day forward,

273
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:44,840
I know not when we shall meet again.

274
00:42:47,383 --> 00:42:49,440
though Hongsawadi and Ayutthaya

275
00:42:50,250 --> 00:42:52,040
may no longer stand as brother states,

276
00:42:56,983 --> 00:42:57,984
you,

277
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:03,760
you shall always be my brother.

278
00:43:47,640 --> 00:43:48,741
[Brother.]

279
00:45:17,523 --> 00:45:19,520
The death of Mingyi Swa

280
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:22,320
caused King Nanda Bayin

281
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:24,760
to be so grief-stricken that he lost his mind.

282
00:46:35,910 --> 00:46:36,911
Afterwards,

283
00:46:37,623 --> 00:46:41,160
Hongsawadi was plunged into great internal turmoil.

284
00:46:56,130 --> 00:46:57,800
King Nanda Bayin

285
00:46:58,320 --> 00:47:01,100
never again led an army to attack Ayutthaya.

286
00:47:34,670 --> 00:47:38,400
Yet the prayer shared between Mingyi Swa and I

287
00:47:39,360 --> 00:47:40,880
has not yet come true.

288
00:47:44,697 --> 00:47:47,597
Humanity continues to wage war,

289
00:47:48,080 --> 00:47:50,120
fighting and struggling against one another.

290
00:48:12,760 --> 00:48:13,761
Even if today,

291
00:48:14,640 --> 00:48:16,680
our dream cannot yet be realized,

292
00:48:18,710 --> 00:48:21,880
in the days to come, people will surely know

293
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:23,840
that peace alone

294
00:48:24,440 --> 00:48:26,720
will bring about eternal happiness.
